title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1992-03-02
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Little Red Rooster, Brown Eyed Women, It's All Over Now, Loser, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums*-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

*with Billy on the jackhammer

reviews.review_text: My First Dead Show. This was my first Grateful Dead show. I was in the parking lot the first night of the 3 night run, I couldn't get out of the van(overdid the chemicals) i miracled a girl in on the first night. However this night was magical. Better than the 3rd night in my opinion. My 2nd dead show.
Nice SBD Good performance, not bad set.
